Description
There are N water tankers initially transporting waterᵢ litres of water each. You are also given the maximum capacity of each tanker in the form of an array capacity.

It is given that water can easily be transferred from one tanker to another. You need to find the minimum number of tankers that can transfer the same amount of water currently being transported by the N tankers.

Input Format
The first line of the input contains one integer T - the number of test cases. Then T test cases follow.

The first line of each test case contains an integer N - the number of tankers.

The second line of each test case contains N space-separated integers water₁, water₂, ..., waterₙ.

The third line of each test case contains N space-separated integers capacity₁, capacity₂, ..., capacityₙ.

Output Format
For each test case, print the minimum number of tankers needed on a new line.

Constraints
1 ≤ T ≤ 10³
1 ≤ N ≤ 10⁵
0 ≤ waterᵢ ≤ capacityᵢ ≤ 10⁹

It's guaranteed that the sum of N over all test cases ≤ 5 × 10⁵.

Sample Input 1
1
3
2 2 2
4 4 4

Sample Output 1
2

Sample Input 2
1
3
8 7 9
10 10 10

Sample Output 2
3

Note

In Sample Input 1,
The total quantity of water being transported is 6L. So, a minimum of 2 containers will be needed.

In Sample Input 2,
A minimum of 3 tankers will be needed in all the cases.



//bruteforce

#include <iostream>
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;
#define endl "\n" // optional, better to avoid redefining endl

void solve()
{
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    vector<int> v(n);

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        cin >> v[i];
    }
    int ans = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        int z = 0;
        int o = 0;
        for (int j = i; j < n; j++)
        {
            if (v[j] == 0)
            {
                z++;
            }
            else
            {
                o++;
            }

            if (z == o)
            {
                ans = max(ans, j - i + 1);
            }
        }
    }
    cout << ans << endl;
}

int main()
{
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--)
    {
        solve();
    }

    return 0;
}


